@section(Moisture Limiting Factor)

Growth limitation due to lack of water is calculated through the "Moisture VegetationLimitingFactor causing Vegetation Growth" model @cite(Allen1998). This model ranges from 0 (limitation of growth due to water stress) to 1 (no limitation of growth due to water). It is based on the model that calculates the degree of water depletion in the root zone, depending on whether the water is at maximum field capacity or reaches its wilt point. Moreover, it is necessary to calculate a balance between inputs (precipitation) and outputs (percolation and evapotranspiration) as well as depth of roots, atmospheric temperature or soil texture.
